WRESTLING TEAM MY FIRST DAY.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.578
NEVER SHOULD HAVE WORN
A TANK TOP WITHOUT A BRA.

11:43.578 --> 11:45.748
YOU SHOULD DRESS DOWDY
LIKE THAT AGAIN TOMORROW--

11:45.748 --> 11:46.832
BE SAFER THAT WAY.

11:46.832 --> 11:48.500
OH, OH, OH.

11:48.500 --> 11:51.754
AND DON'T FORGET TO PEE
BEFORE YOU LEAVE HOME.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.713
BATHROOMS ARE A NIGHTMARE.

11:53.713 --> 11:55.382
UKRAINIAN GIRLS BEAT ME UP
MY FIRST WEEK

11:55.382 --> 11:56.842
BECAUSE I DIDN'T HAVE
ANY CIGARETTES.

11:56.842 --> 11:58.760
LAST TIME I WENT
TO THE LITTLE GIRLS' ROOM

11:58.760 --> 12:01.054
WITHOUT A PACK
OF VIRGINIA SLIMS.

12:01.054 --> 12:02.722
YOU NEED ANY MONEY
FOR SCHOOL SUPPLIES?

12:02.722 --> 12:05.225
I CAN LOAN YOU A FEW DOLLARS
UNTIL FRIDAY IF YOU DO.

12:05.225 --> 12:06.518
- NO, IT'S FINE.

12:06.518 --> 12:08.813
I HAVE STUFF
FROM LAST YEAR, THANKS.

12:08.813 --> 12:11.064
- CARL, HONEY, YOU NEED
ANY MONEY FOR SCHOOL SUPPLIES?

12:11.064 --> 12:13.400
- NAH, I'M JUST GONNA STEAL
STUFF FROM THE WEAKER KIDS.

12:13.400 --> 12:16.319
- STEAL SOME STUFF FOR CHUCKIE
TOO, WOULD YOU PLEASE, SWEETIE?

12:21.909 --> 12:24.244
- WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?
- HE'S CRAZY. HE STEALS BABY.

12:24.244 --> 12:26.163
HE NEEDS TO BE PUT AWAY
INTO CRAZY PEOPLE PLACE

12:26.163 --> 12:28.248
WHERE THEY SPRAY HIM
WITH CRAZY PEOPLE FIRE HOSE

12:28.248 --> 12:29.541
AND PUT ELECTRIC IN HIS HEAD.

12:29.541 --> 12:31.126
- PLEASE, SHUT THE FUCK UP!

12:31.126 --> 12:32.878
I TOLD HIM I WAS GONNA
TAKE HIM TO THE HOSPITAL.

12:32.878 --> 12:34.797
HE FREAKED OUT.
HE TOOK THE FUCKING BABY.

12:34.797 --> 12:36.799
- STOLE THE CAR.
I NEED IT BACK FOR WORK.

12:36.799 --> 12:38.466
- SINCE WHEN
DO YOU HAVE A FUCKING JOB?

12:38.466 --> 12:39.968
- I GOT TO TAKE
THOSE GUNS WE LIFTED

12:39.968 --> 12:41.970
OFF THE MILITIA GEEKS
DOWN TO THE PROJECTS.

12:41.970 --> 12:44.097
I SPENT ALL DAY YESTERDAY
FILING OFF SERIAL NUMBERS.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.099
- TAKE A FUCKING BUS!
- WITH A DOZEN UZIS?

12:46.099 --> 12:48.310
- YEAH! CALL A CAB
OR FUCKING DAVEY OR...

12:48.310 --> 12:50.395
[both shouting in background]
- IAN HAVE A PSYCHOTIC BREAK?

12:50.395 --> 12:52.647
- I THINK SO.

12:52.647 --> 12:53.940
- NO HANDS.

12:53.940 --> 12:56.401
WHOO! WHOO!

12:56.401 --> 12:58.612
[radio crackling]
COME ON. COME ON.

12:58.612 --> 13:00.906
- BACK WITH THE ILLINOIS CROP
REPORT AFTER THESE WORDS FROM--

13:00.906 --> 13:02.324
- ♪ I CAN'T WAIT TO GET
ON THE ROAD AGAIN ♪

13:02.324 --> 13:04.367
- OH. OH.

13:04.367 --> 13:07.662
♪ BUM BUM
ON THE ROAD AGAIN ♪

13:07.662 --> 13:09.289
- ♪ GOING PLACES ♪

13:09.289 --> 13:12.918
- ♪ THAT I'VE NEVER BEEN ♪
HEY, THAT'S US.

13:12.918 --> 13:15.879
[mumbling] ♪ THINGS THAT
I MAY NEVER SEE AGAIN ♪

13:15.879 --> 13:20.050
♪ I CAN'T WAIT TO GET
ON THE ROAD AGAIN ♪

13:20.050 --> 13:21.676
- ♪ ON THE ROAD AGAIN ♪

13:21.676 --> 13:24.721
- OH, SHIT.
LOOK AT THAT.

13:24.721 --> 13:26.389
- ♪ WE GO DOWN THE HIGHWAY ♪

13:26.389 --> 13:28.808
♪ WE'RE THE BEST OF FRIENDS ♪

13:28.808 --> 13:33.188
♪ INSISTING THAT THE WORLD
BE TURNING OUR WAY ♪

13:33.188 --> 13:35.106
♪ AND OUR WAY ♪

13:35.106 --> 13:37.317
♪ IS ON THE ROAD AGAIN ♪

13:37.317 --> 13:40.445
- THE SUNSET'S
FUCKING BEAUTIFUL!

13:40.445 --> 13:42.948
- [crying]
- [howling]

13:42.948 --> 13:45.868
- [wailing]

13:45.868 --> 13:49.997
- WHOO! WHOO!
- [crying]

13:49.997 --> 13:51.373
- WHOO!

13:51.373 --> 13:53.833
- HE TOOK YEVGENY LAST NIGHT?
- LATE, YEAH.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.253
- DID YOU TRY CALLING HIS PHONE?
- YES, HE'S NOT ANSWERING.

13:56.253 --> 13:57.963
- WHO'S IAN,
THE ONE WITH THE RED HAIR?

13:57.963 --> 13:59.965
- YES, SWEETIE, HE'S THE GAY ONE
WITH ALL THE PROBLEMS.

13:59.965 --> 14:01.716
- HIS BEING GAY DOESN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO

14:01.716 --> 14:02.926
WITH HIS PROBLEMS,
OKAY?

14:02.926 --> 14:04.427
- I-I DIDN'T SAY
GAY WAS A PROBLEM,

14:04.427 --> 14:06.179
JUST THAT HE IS GAY
AND HE HAS PROBLEMS.

14:06.179 --> 14:08.139
- HE LEFT, LIKE, 18 HOURS AGO.
HE COULD BE ANYWHERE BY NOW.

14:08.139 --> 14:09.724
- MAYBE HE'S IN COLORADO.
- COLORADO?

14:09.724 --> 14:11.518
WHY WOULD HE BE IN COLORADO?
- FREE WEED.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.853
- NOT FREE, IDIOT.
LEGALIZED.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.313
- SHOULDN'T SOMEBODY
CALL THE POLICE?

14:15.313 --> 14:16.606
all: NO!

14:16.606 --> 14:17.942
[knock at door]

14:17.942 --> 14:19.401
- WEEDS ARE FREE IN COLORADO?

14:19.401 --> 14:20.986
- UH-HUH.
THAT'S RIGHT, SWEETIE.

14:20.986 --> 14:23.989
[pounding on door]

14:23.989 --> 14:25.740
- OH, JESUS.
- WE NEED TO TALK.

14:25.740 --> 14:28.451
- NO, WE DON'T.

14:28.451 --> 14:29.828
- WHAT THE FUCK
IS HE DOING HERE?

14:29.828 --> 14:30.870
- I HAVE NO IDEA.

14:30.870 --> 14:32.247
- HEY, LIP, HOW YOU BEEN?

14:32.247 --> 14:33.707
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE MARRIED.
- I AM.

14:33.707 --> 14:34.874
- YOU'RE MARRIED?
- UH-HUH.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.710
- WHAT? TO WHO?
- TO GUS.

14:36.710 --> 14:38.503
- THE MUSICIAN?
- IS THAT GUS?

14:38.503 --> 14:39.922
- NO, THAT'S JIMMY.
- WHO'S JIMMY?

14:39.922 --> 14:41.423
- HER OLD BOYFRIEND.

14:41.423 --> 14:43.675
- THEN WHO'S GUS?
- WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

14:43.675 --> 14:45.635
- GUS IS AN INCREDIBLE MUSICIAN.

14:45.635 --> 14:47.304
I MET HIM AT WORK,
AND HE'S A GREAT GUY.

14:47.304 --> 14:48.513
- YEAH, MUSICIANS
ARE NOTORIOUSLY

14:48.513 --> 14:49.932
UNRELIABLE HUSBAND MATERIAL.

14:49.932 --> 14:51.433
- OH, SAID THE ASSHOLE
WHO DISAPPEARS

14:51.433 --> 14:53.518
FROM THE FACE OF THE EARTH
FOR YEARS AT A TIME.

14:53.518 --> 14:55.020
- WHEN DID YOU GET MARRIED?

14:55.020 --> 14:56.730
- A FEW DAYS AGO.

14:56.730 --> 14:58.064
- AND YOU'VE BEEN
KEEPING IT A SECRET?

14:58.064 --> 15:00.109
WHY?
- EXCELLENT QUESTION.

15:00.109 --> 15:03.778
WHY KEEP WONDERFUL MUSICIAN GUS
A SECRET IF HE'S SO GREAT?

15:03.778 --> 15:05.613
- OUT. NOW.

15:05.613 --> 15:07.907
[door opens and closes]

15:07.907 --> 15:10.076
- [grunts]

15:10.076 --> 15:12.037
- YOU CAN'T JUST
KEEP SHOWING UP.

15:12.037 --> 15:13.621
- WHO'S THE LOUD BLONDE
WITH THE KID?

15:13.621 --> 15:15.623
- SHE'S A NEW HALF-SISTER.
- REALLY?

15:15.623 --> 15:16.916
- YEAH.
- FRANK OR MONICA'S?

15:16.916 --> 15:19.044
- YOU GOT TO CALL FIRST.

15:19.044 --> 15:21.421
- HALF-SISTER.
WHAT ELSE I MISS?

15:21.421 --> 15:23.840
- A LOT, OKAY?
EVERYTHING.

15:23.840 --> 15:26.092
- LIKE?
- LIKE LIAM ALMOST DYING.

15:26.092 --> 15:29.013
- LIAM ALMOST DIED?
W-WHAT HAPPENED?

15:29.013 --> 15:31.140
- I LEFT OUT SOME COKE
THAT THIS ASSHOLE

15:31.140 --> 15:32.932
THAT I WASN'T REALLY DATING
GAVE ME,

15:32.932 --> 15:34.726
AND HE GOT INTO IT.

15:34.726 --> 15:37.771
HE'S FINE.

15:37.771 --> 15:39.147
PUT ME IN JAIL.

15:39.147 --> 15:41.274
- YOU WENT TO JAIL?
- YEAH.

15:41.274 --> 15:43.318
- NO SHIT.

15:43.318 --> 15:45.154
- NO SHIT.

15:45.154 --> 15:46.321
- AND YOU GOT MARRIED.

15:46.321 --> 15:48.073
- YEAH, I GOT MARRIED.

15:48.073 --> 15:51.368
- TO A 35-YEAR-OLD BASS PLAYER
NAMED GUS PFENDER.

15:51.368 --> 15:52.744
- HOW DO YOU EVEN KNOW THAT?

15:52.744 --> 15:54.245
ARE YOU, LIKE, SPYING ON ME?

15:54.245 --> 15:55.955
- NO.
WELL, SORT OF.

15:55.955 --> 15:58.666
ANGELA.

15:58.666 --> 16:01.086
DO YOU LOVE HIM?

16:01.086 --> 16:02.629
- YOU DON'T GET TO ASK ME THAT.

16:02.629 --> 16:03.963
- I LOVE YOU.

16:03.963 --> 16:07.051
- OH, FUCK YOU.
- I LOVE YOU.

16:07.051 --> 16:08.718
DO YOU STILL LOVE ME?

16:08.718 --> 16:10.095
- NO.

16:10.095 --> 16:12.055
- LIAR.

16:12.055 --> 16:13.973
- I DON'T.

16:16.143 --> 16:17.435
- I LOVE YOU.

16:20.647 --> 16:22.982
- [sighs]

16:22.982 --> 16:24.484
- [whispers]
I LOVE YOU.

16:29.572 --> 16:32.283
- [quietly]
DON'T DO IT.

16:32.283 --> 16:33.535
DON'T DO IT.

16:33.535 --> 16:35.370
- NO.
- [groans]

16:35.370 --> 16:37.539
- FIONA.

16:37.539 --> 16:39.083
- SHIT.

16:49.176 --> 16:51.594
- HOT.

16:51.594 --> 16:54.139
VERY HOT.

16:54.139 --> 16:57.142
[folk music]

16:57.142 --> 17:05.067
♪ ♪

17:06.109 --> 17:10.155
[phone vibrates]

17:10.155 --> 17:18.205
♪ ♪

17:32.510 --> 17:33.928
- JIMMY SPENT THE NIGHT?

17:33.928 --> 17:36.181
- YEAH.

17:36.181 --> 17:37.432
DID YOU HEAR ANYTHING FROM IAN?

17:37.432 --> 17:39.184
- NO. YOU?

17:39.184 --> 17:41.270
- NO.

17:41.270 --> 17:42.437
- YOU GOT THIS ONE?

17:42.437 --> 17:44.105
- YEAH.
- ARE YOU SURE?

17:44.105 --> 17:45.982
'CAUSE I COULD BEAT HIM TO DEATH
WITH A BASEBALL BAT.

17:45.982 --> 17:47.609
YOU KNOW, SAY I MISTOOK HIM
FOR AN INTRUDER.

17:47.609 --> 17:49.444
- NO, I'M GOOD.
- ALL RIGHT.

17:49.444 --> 17:50.987
- THANKS, LITTLE BROTHER.

17:50.987 --> 17:53.156
- NO WORRIES, BIG SISTER.

17:53.156 --> 17:55.658
READY TO GET DRESSED?
[grunts]

18:08.171 --> 18:09.547
- WHAT?

18:09.547 --> 18:10.840
- NO, NOTHING.

18:12.717 --> 18:14.177
- THANKS.

18:14.177 --> 18:19.224
- SO...IS JIMMY GONNA
MOVE IN WITH YOU AND GUS?

18:19.224 --> 18:21.309
- WHAT?
- GETTING YOUR OWN PLACE?

18:21.309 --> 18:23.770
- WE HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

18:23.770 --> 18:24.979
- I KNOW HOW IMPORTANT

18:24.979 --> 18:27.190
THOSE EARLY DAYS
OF MARRIAGE ARE.

18:27.190 --> 18:30.235
FIGURING EACH OTHER OUT,
GETTING USED TO COMPROMISE.

18:30.235 --> 18:32.445
MORE EGGS, CARL?
CHUCKIE, HONEY?

18:32.445 --> 18:34.197
- HAS MICKEY HEARD ANYTHING
FROM IAN?

18:34.197 --> 18:36.074
- NO, I CALLED.
NOTHING.

18:36.074 --> 18:38.368
- IF YOU AND GUS DO DECIDE
TO GET YOUR OWN PLACE,

18:38.368 --> 18:40.203
DON'T WORRY ABOUT US HERE.

18:40.203 --> 18:42.664
I CAN FILL IN NOW AND THEN
AS NEEDED.

18:42.664 --> 18:44.499
- OH, GOT TO GO. SCHOOL.
[knock at door]

18:44.499 --> 18:46.167
- SHOOT--HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT,
I GOT TO GO TOO.

18:46.167 --> 18:48.169
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE WORKING
FRESHMAN ORIENTATION.

18:48.169 --> 18:49.462
- YOU'RE GOING?
- YEAH.

18:49.462 --> 18:50.838
I'LL HAVE MY PHONE THOUGH.

18:50.838 --> 18:52.131
[knock at door]
- CARL.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.841
DOOR. GO.

18:56.094 --> 18:58.846
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.
LUNCH.

18:58.846 --> 19:00.932
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

19:00.932 --> 19:03.227
BETTER SAFE THAN SORRY.

19:03.227 --> 19:05.603
AND NO BATHROOMS, RIGHT?

19:05.603 --> 19:07.480
- SCHOOL STARTS TODAY?
- MM-HMM.

19:07.480 --> 19:09.023
- HIGH SCHOOL.
HER FIRST DAY.

19:09.023 --> 19:12.277
- DEBS, HIGH SCHOOL!
THIS IS SO EXCITING.

19:12.277 --> 19:14.112
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE A BLAST.

19:14.112 --> 19:16.198
- YEAH, THAT HUSBAND GUY'S
AT THAT FRONT DOOR.

19:17.240 --> 19:19.326
- GO.
GO, I GOT THIS.

19:19.326 --> 19:21.786
GO DEAL WITH YOUR LIFE.

19:21.786 --> 19:23.871
- HEY.
- HEY, I'VE BEEN TEXTING YOU.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.040
- MY PHONE DIED.
I'M SORRY.

19:28.626 --> 19:30.461
- UH...
- UH, THAT'S FRANK.

19:30.461 --> 19:32.297
- FRANK?
- THAT'S MY USELESS FATHER.

19:32.297 --> 19:33.965
- IS THAT SMELL HIM?
- YEAH.

19:33.965 --> 19:35.300
YOU GET USED TO IT.

19:35.300 --> 19:37.302
IT'S LIKE WORKING AT A LANDFILL.

19:37.302 --> 19:38.845
- YOU OKAY?
- YEAH.

19:38.845 --> 19:40.264
IAN STOLE A BABY.

19:40.264 --> 19:41.431
- UH, WHO'S IAN?

19:41.431 --> 19:42.974
- MY BROTHER.
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HIM.

19:42.974 --> 19:44.684
- OH, RIGHT,
THE ONE WHO'S IN COLLEGE.

19:44.684 --> 19:46.769
- NO, NO, NO, THE ONE THAT
RAN AWAY AND JOINED THE ARMY.

19:46.769 --> 19:48.187
- WAIT, NOW...
AND HE STOLE A BABY?

19:48.187 --> 19:49.856
- WELL, HE MORE,
LIKE, BORROWED IT.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.941
IT'S HIS BOYFRIEND'S BAB
- HI, GUS. DEBBIE.

19:51.941 --> 19:53.276
- OH, YEAH, I-I REMEMBER.

19:53.276 --> 19:54.986
- UM, CONGRATULATIONS.

19:54.986 --> 19:56.321
GREAT. I GOT TO GO.
- [laughs]

19:56.321 --> 19:57.363
- FIRST DAY OF HIGH SCHOOL.

19:57.363 --> 19:58.698
- WHA--

19:58.698 --> 20:00.199
- HEY, YOU GUS?

20:00.199 --> 20:02.201
- YEAH.
- ALL RIGHT, I'M LIP, BROTHER.

20:02.201 --> 20:03.995
DON'T FUCK THIS UP 'CAUSE
SHE'S REALLY GREAT, ALL RIGHT?

20:03.995 --> 20:05.747
AND IF I HEAR ANYTHING FROM IAN,
I'LL CALL YOU.

20:05.747 --> 20:08.499
VICE VERSA, RIGHT?
- YEAH.

20:08.499 --> 20:12.587
- OH, HEY, UH, LISTEN,
I-I'M SUPPOSED TO MEET CHRIS

20:12.587 --> 20:15.048
TO HELP WORK ON SOME BACKGROUND
TRACKS FOR HIS DEMO,

20:15.048 --> 20:16.425
BUT I CAN BLOW HIM OFF.

20:16.425 --> 20:17.925
- NO, THANKS, REALLY.

20:17.925 --> 20:19.427
NO, THERE'S NOTHING TO DO HERE
BUT WAIT.

20:19.427 --> 20:21.012
I'LL CALL YOU LATER,

20:21.012 --> 20:22.347
LET YOU KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH IAN?

20:22.347 --> 20:23.723
- YEAH.

20:35.443 --> 20:36.486
- [sighs]

20:39.405 --> 20:42.408
- [wailing]

20:45.787 --> 20:48.790
[screaming]

20:51.584 --> 20:53.294
- [coughing]

20:53.294 --> 20:56.297
- [wailing]

20:59.676 --> 21:02.762
- GOOD MORNING, ILLINOIS.

21:04.347 --> 21:08.435
HEY, WHY YOU CRYING?

21:08.435 --> 21:10.895
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL MORNING,
DON'T YOU KNOW?

21:10.895 --> 21:13.690
OKAY, YOU NEED A NEW DIAPER,
DON'T YOU?

21:14.774 --> 21:17.193
SHH. ALL RIGHT.

21:17.193 --> 21:19.278
HEY, HEY, HEY.
[shushing]

21:19.278 --> 21:21.323
YOU'RE GONNA SCARE MR. SUN AWAY.

21:21.323 --> 21:24.117
OKAY.

21:24.117 --> 21:27.120
- [wailing]

21:34.836 --> 21:36.379
- OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

21:38.381 --> 21:39.716
UH...

21:39.716 --> 21:41.634
OKAY, OKAY.

21:41.634 --> 21:44.513
DIAPERS.

21:44.513 --> 21:46.305
WHERE ARE DIAPERS?

21:51.894 --> 21:53.480
DIAPER.

21:55.482 --> 21:56.566
NO DIAPER.

21:58.317 --> 22:01.362
HEY, YEVVY, LOOK WHAT I FOUND.

22:01.362 --> 22:03.281
MOTORHEAD, YEAH.

22:03.281 --> 22:04.574
HEAVY METAL DIAPER.

22:04.574 --> 22:06.535
[grunting]

22:06.535 --> 22:08.119
YOU'RE GONNA BE A BIG BADASS.

22:08.119 --> 22:10.246
ALL THE OTHER BABIES
ARE GONNA LOOK AT YOU,

22:10.246 --> 22:13.500
AND YOU'RE SUCH A BIG BADASS,
THEY'RE GONNA GO RUNNING--

22:13.500 --> 22:15.793
NO, CRAWLING AWAY IN FEAR.

22:18.087 --> 22:19.756
WHY ARE YOU STILL CRYING?

22:19.756 --> 22:21.883
OH.
YOU'RE HUNGRY.

22:21.883 --> 22:23.176
IT'S MORNING.

22:23.176 --> 22:24.552
BABIES GET HUNGRY
IN THE MORNING.

22:28.931 --> 22:30.725
UH...

22:30.725 --> 22:34.145
NO FOOD,
BUT WE'RE NEAR AN AQUEDUCT.

22:34.145 --> 22:35.480
WE CAN FORAGE.

22:35.480 --> 22:37.523
WE CAN HUNT.

22:37.523 --> 22:41.486
WE CAN GET WILD GREENS, OKAY?

22:41.486 --> 22:42.528
[in deep voice]
WE GO NOW.

22:42.528 --> 22:44.781
WE HUNT LIKE MEN.

22:44.781 --> 22:46.157
ONE, TWO, THREE.

22:46.157 --> 22:48.576
UP, UP, AND AWAY.
[phone ringing]

22:48.576 --> 22:52.955
LEFT, LEFT,
LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT.

22:52.955 --> 22:54.540
- ALL RIGHT, SHITHEAD,
THIS IS, LIKE,

22:54.540 --> 22:56.501
THE 200TH TIME I'M CALLING
AND YOU NOT PICKING UP.

22:56.501 --> 22:58.419
I'M STARTING
TO GET FUCKING HOMICIDAL.

22:58.419 --> 23:00.421
CALL ME THE FUCK BACK, IAN.

23:03.049 --> 23:05.927
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

23:05.927 --> 23:09.556
I LOVE YOU.

23:09.556 --> 23:12.266
CALL ME BACK.

23:12.266 --> 23:13.560
- I CALL NIKA TO TAKE ME.

23:13.560 --> 23:15.269
- WHAT?
- HOSPITAL.

23:15.269 --> 23:18.523
CONTRACTIONS AND WATER BREAKS
ON SOFA WHILE I WATCH TV.

23:18.523 --> 23:19.649
- NICE OUTFIT.
YOU A MORMON NOW?

23:19.649 --> 23:21.317
- I HAVE TO WEAR
SHITTY, BORING CLOTHES

23:21.317 --> 23:22.735
FOR SURROGATE BABY PARENTS.

23:22.735 --> 23:24.237
WHEN I'M DONE SELLING THIS BABY,

23:24.237 --> 23:25.947
I WANT MY YEVGENY
BACK IN MY BED

23:25.947 --> 23:27.449
TO SLEEP WHERE HE BELONGS.

23:27.449 --> 23:28.991
IN MY BED, OR I CALL THE COPS.

23:28.991 --> 23:30.827
- OH, MY FU--YOU NEED TO STOP
WITH THE COPS.

23:30.827 --> 23:32.703
NO COPS.
- YES, COPS.

23:32.703 --> 23:33.913
[knock at door]
[door opens]

23:36.541 --> 23:37.917
- YEVGENY?
- [speaking Russian]

23:37.917 --> 23:39.794
- NO, NO.
NO MORE FUCKING RUSSIAN EITHER.

23:39.794 --> 23:41.587
I HATE
THAT BORIS AND NATASHA SHIT.

23:41.587 --> 23:44.633
YOU GET THE MONEY
BEFORE YOU HAND THE BABY OVER.

23:44.633 --> 23:47.469
WE DON'T TAKE PERSONAL CHECKS
OR PAY-YOU-IN-INSTALLMENTS CRAP.

23:47.469 --> 23:50.429
WE TAKE CASH
OR CASHIER'S CHECK OR WHATEVER.

23:50.429 --> 23:52.640
OR WE FIND SOME OTHER
INFERTILE YUPPIE IDIOT

23:52.640 --> 23:54.267
TO BUY YOUR BROKEN CONDOM KID.

23:54.267 --> 23:57.186
- NO YEVGENY, THEN COPS.

24:15.621 --> 24:17.540
- GO.
- [grunts]

24:17.540 --> 24:19.626
- GET OUT. NOW.

24:19.626 --> 24:22.420
I WANT YOU OUT NOW.

24:22.420 --> 24:23.504
- ALL RIGHT.

24:29.051 --> 24:30.428
[door slams]

24:35.433 --> 24:36.559
MORNING.

24:38.436 --> 24:39.478
ANY COFFEE?

24:46.986 --> 24:50.448
[door opens and closes]
- I THINK I REALLY FUCKED UP.

24:50.448 --> 24:52.783
- KEV AND I ARE SEPARATING.
- WHAT?

24:52.783 --> 24:54.243
- HE DOESN'T EVEN NOTICE
I'M ALIVE.

24:54.243 --> 24:55.786
HE HAS NO SEX DRIVE.

24:55.786 --> 24:57.496
THE ONLY THING HE CARES ABOUT
IS THE DAMN BABIES.

24:57.496 --> 25:00.625
- KEV MOVED OUT?
- NO, COUCH.

25:00.625 --> 25:02.501
CAN YOU EVEN SAY
THAT YOU'RE MARRIED TO SOMEONE

25:02.501 --> 25:04.420
IF YOU'RE NOT HAVING SEX?

25:04.420 --> 25:07.006
IT'S LIKE ALIENS
ABDUCTED HIS BODY

25:07.006 --> 25:08.758
WHILE I WAS IN LABOR
AND REPLACED HIM

25:08.758 --> 25:10.843
WITH SOMEONE
WHO LOOKS LIKE KEV,

25:10.843 --> 25:12.762
TALKS LIKE KEV,
BUT ISN'T KEV.

25:12.762 --> 25:14.972
- WHAT ABOUT THE BABIES?

25:14.972 --> 25:17.183
- I DON'T KNOW.
THIS JUST ISN'T WORKING FOR ME.

25:17.183 --> 25:19.603
- NO, I MEAN WHERE ARE THEY?

25:19.603 --> 25:21.812
- KEVIN AND I GOT IN A FIGHT,
AND THEN THEY STARTED CRYING.

25:21.812 --> 25:23.981
THEN HE STARTED YELLING AT ME
BECAUSE THEY WERE CRYING,

25:23.981 --> 25:25.483
LIKE IT WAS ONLY MY FAULT,

25:25.483 --> 25:27.443
AND THE ONLY WAY
I CAN GET HIM TO EVEN LOOK AT ME

25:27.443 --> 25:29.570
IS IF I KNOCK HIM
UPSIDE THE HEAD WITH A PAN.

25:29.570 --> 25:31.615
- YOU HIT HIM IN THE HEAD
WITH A PAN?

25:31.615 --> 25:33.032
- NO.
HELL, NO.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.325
WHOSE DAMN SIDE ARE YOU ON?

25:34.325 --> 25:35.576
- I'M NOT ON ANYONE'S SIDE.

25:35.576 --> 25:36.911
- NO?
WELL, YOU BETTER BE,

25:36.911 --> 25:38.245
AND THE SIDE BETTER BE MY SIDE.

25:38.245 --> 25:40.247
- OKAY. OKAY--
SURE, OF COURSE.

25:40.247 --> 25:42.667
SO WHERE ARE KEVIN
AND THE GIRLS?

25:42.667 --> 25:44.835
- WE STARTED FIGHTING, AND THEN
HE TOOK THEM TO THE PARK

25:44.835 --> 25:47.463
BECAUSE THEY COME FIRST, ALWAYS.

25:47.463 --> 25:50.759
SHIT.
I GOT TO GO.

25:50.759 --> 25:52.885
I GOT TO GO TAKE A SHOWER
AND GO TO THE ALIBI AND OPEN UP.

25:52.885 --> 25:54.845
WHAT DID YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT?

25:54.845 --> 25:56.138
- NOTHING.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.556
WE CAN CATCH UP LATER.

25:57.556 --> 25:58.975
- THANK YOU.

26:01.268 --> 26:03.437
I LOVE YOU.
- LOVE YOU TOO.

26:09.611 --> 26:11.320
[sighs]

26:11.320 --> 26:14.323
[rock music]

26:14.323 --> 26:18.494
♪ ♪

26:18.494 --> 26:20.747
- ♪ I DON'T SET OUT
TO PLEASE THEM ♪

26:20.747 --> 26:22.456
♪ GOD I DON'T NEED THEM ♪

26:22.456 --> 26:25.167
♪ GOTTA BE SOMETHING IN THE FOOD
THAT THEY FEED ♪

26:25.167 --> 26:28.254
♪ BUT HOW DO YOU PLAY WITH
THE HAND THAT YOU'RE DEALT ♪

26:28.254 --> 26:32.717
♪ IT JUST DON'T FEEL RIGHT ♪

26:32.717 --> 26:35.094
- YOU DEADLY DEBBIE?
- HUH?

26:35.094 --> 26:38.597
- YOU KNOW, FROM YOUTUBE,
KICKING THOSE TWO GIRLS' ASSES?

26:38.597 --> 26:40.474
- YEAH.

26:40.474 --> 26:42.393
THAT WAS ME.

26:42.393 --> 26:44.603
- YOU THINK YOU CAN KICK MY ASS?

26:44.603 --> 26:47.314
- YO, DEADLY DEBBIE.

26:47.314 --> 26:49.150
JESUS, I SHOWED YOU
A COUPLE OF MOVES.

26:49.150 --> 26:51.694
DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE GONNA
GO ALL CHUCK NORRIS ON ME.

26:51.694 --> 26:53.571
HEY, GABOWSKI.
HOW WAS YOUR SUMMER?

26:53.571 --> 26:55.031
YOU, UH, FINISH
THE COMMUNITY SERVICE HOURS

26:55.031 --> 26:56.365
FOR THAT SOLICITATION BEEF?

26:56.365 --> 26:57.742
- FUCK YOU, DEREK.

26:57.742 --> 26:59.243
- YEAH, WOULDN'T YOU LIKE TO?

26:59.243 --> 27:02.663
BUT I HEAR
YOU'RE BEHIND ON YOUR SHOTS.

27:02.663 --> 27:04.165
- LATER, DEBBIE.

27:06.793 --> 27:08.377
- MAKING ENEMIES ALREADY?

27:08.377 --> 27:11.464
- SHE WANTED ME TO KICK HER ASS.
- YOU'RE FAMOUS NOW.

27:11.464 --> 27:12.840
LOTS OF IDIOTS
ARE GONNA WANT TO TRY YOU,

27:12.840 --> 27:14.300
GET IT UP ON THE WEB.

27:14.300 --> 27:16.052
- THINK I CAN?
- KICK HER ASS?

27:16.052 --> 27:17.803
YOU THINK YOU CAN?

27:17.803 --> 27:19.848
- I DON'T KNOW.

27:19.848 --> 27:21.932
- I CAN GO, MAYBE.

27:21.932 --> 27:24.143
- THANKS.
- YOU DIDN'T FIND HIM?

27:24.143 --> 27:25.770
- NAH.
- YOU COMING OR NOT?

27:25.770 --> 27:27.354
- UH, NOT.

27:27.354 --> 27:29.023
- WE NEED BATH TOWELS.
- CAN YOU GO WITHOUT ME?

27:29.023 --> 27:30.734
I'LL REIMBURSE YOU FOR MY HALF.

27:32.861 --> 27:34.236
- WHITE WORK?
- WHITE'S GREAT.

27:34.236 --> 27:36.865
THANKS, MUFF.
APPRECIATE IT.

27:39.325 --> 27:40.744
- THE HELL WAS THAT?

27:40.744 --> 27:42.119
- I THINK
SHE'S INTERESTED IN ME.

27:42.119 --> 27:43.829
- YEAH, NO SHIT.
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO ABOUT IT?

27:43.829 --> 27:45.247
- I DON'T KNOW.

27:45.247 --> 27:47.876
IT'S KIND OF INTRIGUING.
- REALLY?

27:47.876 --> 27:49.376
- WELL, ISN'T THAT
WHAT COLLEGE IS ALL ABOUT?

27:49.376 --> 27:51.003
CHECKING OUT A BUNCH
OF DIFFERENT THINGS,

27:51.003 --> 27:53.589
KEEPING YOURSELF
OPEN TO NEW HORIZONS?

27:53.589 --> 27:55.717
HANG ON A SEC.

27:55.717 --> 27:57.468
THIS IS NO INTEREST?

27:57.468 --> 27:59.845
- FOR THE FIRST SIX MONTHS,
$3,000 CREDIT LIMIT TO START,

27:59.845 --> 28:02.598
AND YOU GET
10,000 FREQUENT FLYER MILES.

28:02.598 --> 28:03.724
- DO YOU NEED
ANOTHER CREDIT CARD?

28:03.724 --> 28:05.184
- I NEED A CREDIT CARD.

28:05.184 --> 28:07.019
DAD TOOK AWAY ALL MY CARDS
AFTER THAT THING

28:07.019 --> 28:09.563
WITH THE PRADA BAG AND THEN H&M.

28:10.689 --> 28:12.399
- WHAT,
THEY JUST GIVE YOU A CARD?

28:12.399 --> 28:14.193
- THEY'LL GIVE YOU, LIKE,
TEN IF YOU WANT.

28:14.193 --> 28:15.820
WE'RE THE FUTURE.
THEY'RE METH DEALERS.

28:15.820 --> 28:17.947
GIVE YOU YOUR FIRST FEW HITS
FOR FREE, GET YOU HOOKED.

28:17.947 --> 28:20.116
I'M JUST GONNA RUN IT UP AND
THEN BEG DADDY TO PAY IT OFF,

28:20.116 --> 28:21.826
TURN ON THE TEARS,
TELL HIM HOW MUCH I LOVE HIM,

28:21.826 --> 28:23.369
PROMISE TO COME HOME
FOR CHRISTMAS.

28:23.369 --> 28:24.829
HE ALWAYS CAVES.

28:24.829 --> 28:26.790
- YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA CATCH UP
WITH YOU, OKAY?

28:26.790 --> 28:28.415
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.
- OKAY.

28:36.257 --> 28:38.759
- HEY, IAN, IT'S LIP.
WHERE THE FUCK ARE YOU?

28:38.759 --> 28:41.178
FUCK.

28:41.178 --> 28:43.472
[tools whirring]

28:53.482 --> 28:56.235
- HELLO, LITTLE MAN.
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

29:01.907 --> 29:03.159
HELLO.

29:03.159 --> 29:04.786
- [whimpering]

29:04.786 --> 29:07.580
- OH, HEY, I'M THINKING
I WANT SOME APPLESAUCE.

29:07.580 --> 29:10.207
WANT SOME APPLESAUCE?
- [crying]

29:10.207 --> 29:12.836
- YOU LIKE THAT?
MAYBE SOME PEAS?

29:12.836 --> 29:14.962
I'M GETTING SOME RED BULL TOO.

29:14.962 --> 29:16.505
THAT'S NOT FOR YOU, THOUGH.

29:16.505 --> 29:18.382
OKAY, THERE IT IS.

29:19.466 --> 29:21.218
ALL RIGHT.

29:21.218 --> 29:23.888
PEAS AND THANK YOU.

29:23.888 --> 29:27.892
ALL RIGHT,
AND $20 ON NUMBER ONE, PLEASE.

29:27.892 --> 29:29.226
THANKS.

29:32.938 --> 29:35.149
RIGHT.
UH...

29:37.818 --> 29:39.778
CAN YOU--
CAN YOU JUST HOLD HIM?

29:42.239 --> 29:46.035
HERE, THAT'S, UH...
15, 16, 17, 18, 19.

29:46.035 --> 29:50.956
UH...60...

29:50.956 --> 29:54.835
5--7.
67.

29:54.835 --> 29:56.170
OKAY, THAT'S NOT ENOUGH, RIGHT?

29:56.170 --> 29:57.963
- RIGHT.

29:57.963 --> 30:00.967
- UM...NO, NO.

30:00.967 --> 30:02.509
AND I'M JUST GONNA GET--

30:02.509 --> 30:04.595
CAN I GET A COUPLE DIAPERS,
NOT THE WHOLE PACK?

30:04.595 --> 30:05.972
- NO.

30:05.972 --> 30:07.974
- OKAY, HOW MUCH
DO I HAVE LEFT FOR GAS

30:07.974 --> 30:10.351
IF I JUST DON'T GET ANY DIAPERS?

30:10.351 --> 30:12.353
- $9.27.
- OKAY, $9.27 ON NUMBER ONE.

30:12.353 --> 30:14.022
THANK YOU.
- HANG ON. HANG ON A MINUTE.

30:14.022 --> 30:15.731
UM...HERE.

30:17.107 --> 30:20.110
HERE'S $5 FOR THE DIAPERS.
- OKAY.

30:20.110 --> 30:21.528
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

30:21.528 --> 30:22.988
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE VERY NICE.

30:22.988 --> 30:24.949
YOU'RE A VERY, VERY NICE LADY.
THANK YOU.

30:24.949 --> 30:26.825
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
- NO, NO, REALLY, IT'S--WOW.

30:26.825 --> 30:28.995
YOU'RE AMAZING.
YOU'RE VERY NICE.

30:28.995 --> 30:31.538
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
THANK YOU.

30:31.538 --> 30:32.831
ALL RIGHT.

30:32.831 --> 30:36.377
OKAY, HERE WE GO.
- [crying]

30:38.922 --> 30:42.841
- [stammering]
YOU CAN'T DO THAT HERE.

30:42.841 --> 30:44.843
YOU CAN'T CHANGE HIM HERE.

30:44.843 --> 30:46.637
- RIGHT.

30:46.637 --> 30:48.889
OKAY.

30:48.889 --> 30:50.224
THANK YOU.

30:52.518 --> 30:53.894
BYE-BYE, NICE LADY.

30:53.894 --> 30:56.021
CAN YOU SAY "BYE-BYE"?
BYE-BYE.

30:56.021 --> 30:58.649
BYE-BYE, NICE LADY.
THANK YOU.

30:58.649 --> 30:59.943
HEY, THANKS, MAN.

31:04.571 --> 31:05.864
- ORDER UP.

31:05.864 --> 31:07.741
- TWO MORE FRIES AND A BLT.

31:07.741 --> 31:09.994
- YOUR HUSBAND, GUS, CAME IN
LOOKING FOR YOU THIS MORNING.

31:09.994 --> 31:11.578
- THANKS.
I SAW HIM.

31:11.578 --> 31:12.997
- SO HE FOUND YOU?
- YEP.

31:12.997 --> 31:14.665
AND A REUBEN, LIGHT KRAUT.

31:14.665 --> 31:16.083
- SO WHO WAS THE GUY
YOU WERE BEATING

31:16.083 --> 31:18.210
THE SHIT OUT OF YESTERDAY?

31:18.210 --> 31:20.004
- OLD BOYFRIEND.

31:20.004 --> 31:22.006
- DID YOU SLEEP WITH HIM?

31:22.006 --> 31:23.465
MM.

31:23.465 --> 31:25.092
I FIGURED YOU MUST HAVE
AFTER YOU PUNCHED HIM

31:25.092 --> 31:26.928
IN THE FACE SIX TIMES.

31:29.305 --> 31:32.599
HEY, UH, JACKIE'S GETTING OUT
OF THE HOSPITAL THIS AFTERNOON.

31:32.599 --> 31:35.061
- ALREADY?
YOU PICKING HER UP?

31:35.061 --> 31:37.021
- NO. HER PAROLE OFFICER.

31:37.021 --> 31:39.440
- WHAT? WHY?
YOU CALLED HER?

31:39.440 --> 31:41.442
- IT'S PART OF THE DEAL
HIRING HER.

31:41.442 --> 31:43.902
GOT TO CALL THE P.O.
IF SHE RELAPSES.

31:43.902 --> 31:45.446
- FUCK THAT.

31:45.446 --> 31:47.364
SHE'S TRYING.
GIVE HER ANOTHER CHANCE.

31:47.364 --> 31:49.783
- SHE'S HAD PLENTY, AND I'M NOT
GONNA BE THE ONE ENABLING HER.

31:49.783 --> 31:51.952
IF SHE VIOLATES PAROLE,
SHE GOES BACK.

31:51.952 --> 31:54.246
HEY.
GIRLFRIEND'S HERE.

31:54.246 --> 31:55.706
- OH, SHIT.

31:55.706 --> 31:57.124
- I THOUGHT
THAT WAS YOUR BIG TIPPER.

31:57.124 --> 31:59.084
- UH, YEAH.
IT'S COMPLICATED.

31:59.084 --> 32:02.088
- IT ALWAYS IS WITH YOU.

32:02.088 --> 32:04.048
ORDER UP.
[bell dings]

32:09.094 --> 32:12.015
- COFFEE AND A PIECE
OF PEACH PIE YOU WON'T EAT?

32:12.015 --> 32:15.434
- I THINK I'LL LEAVE THE APPLE
A LA MODE UNTOUCHED TODAY.

32:17.936 --> 32:19.355
- ARE YOU AND JIMMY LOVERS?

32:19.355 --> 32:22.150
- NO, HE'S NOT MY TYPE.

32:22.150 --> 32:23.275
YOU'RE MY TYPE.

32:23.275 --> 32:24.693
- [chuckles]
I PICKED UP ON THAT.

32:24.693 --> 32:26.154
- REALLY?

32:26.154 --> 32:27.488
I'M USUALLY PRETTY GOOD
AT HIDING IT.

32:27.488 --> 32:28.781
- WHY ARE YOU HERE?

32:28.781 --> 32:30.741
- I NEED HIM TO MAKE A DECISION.

32:30.741 --> 32:33.035
IF HE STAYS, I HAVE TO MAKE
OTHER ARRANGEMENTS.

32:33.035 --> 32:35.120
- OTHER ARRANGEMENTS FOR WHAT?

32:35.120 --> 32:37.164
- BUSINESS.

32:37.164 --> 32:39.666
SO IS HE GONNA STAY?

32:41.543 --> 32:44.338
- I DON'T KNOW.

32:44.338 --> 32:47.674
I DON'T KNOW IF HE'S GONNA STAY.

32:47.674 --> 32:49.802
- WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
DOESN'T CARE IF THEY'RE CRYING

32:49.802 --> 32:52.180
OR IF THEY'RE GETTING A RASH
OR IF THEY'RE NOT SLEEPING

32:52.180 --> 32:53.931
OR IF WE'RE GIVING THEM
ENOUGH EYE CONTACT,

32:53.931 --> 32:55.974
WORRYING ABOUT
IF THE HOUSE IS EVEN SAFE?

32:55.974 --> 32:58.227
THEY CAN HANG THEMSELVES
ON CURTAIN STRINGS.

32:58.227 --> 33:00.146
ELECTRICAL OUTLETS
ARE A NIGHTMARE.

33:00.146 --> 33:02.147
TOILETS? TOILETS?
TOILETS.

33:02.147 --> 33:03.982
KIDS DROWN IN TOILETS
ALL THE TIME.

33:03.982 --> 33:05.275
CLOSE THE LID.

33:05.275 --> 33:07.694
YOU GOT TO BE ON IT
ALL THE TIME.

33:07.694 --> 33:11.199
I MEAN, WHAT KIND OF PERSON
DOESN'T WORRY ABOUT THIS SHIT?

33:11.199 --> 33:12.366
MY WIFE, THAT'S WHO.

33:12.366 --> 33:13.700
THAT'S WHO DOESN'T WORRY.

33:13.700 --> 33:15.369
NO, SLEEPS RIGHT
THROUGH THE NIGHT.

33:15.369 --> 33:17.996
WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
CAN SLEEP THROUGH

33:17.996 --> 33:19.373
HER CHILDREN CRYING, HUH?

33:19.373 --> 33:21.084
WHAT KIND OF PERSON?

33:21.084 --> 33:23.502
JULIE?
WHAT KIND, HUH?

33:23.502 --> 33:25.337
- YOU KNOW THAT ME
JERKING YOU OFF WAS

33:25.337 --> 33:27.005
A ONE-TIME THING, RIGHT?

33:43.105 --> 33:44.398
- CAROL?

33:44.398 --> 33:45.983
SVETLANA'S ASKING FOR YOU.

33:45.983 --> 33:47.317
SHE ONLY WANTS MRS. HEWITT.

33:47.317 --> 33:48.735
WE'LL COME GET YOU
WHEN IT'S TIME.

33:48.735 --> 33:50.988
- OH, OKAY.

34:00.372 --> 34:03.292
[rock music]

34:03.292 --> 34:06.753
♪ ♪

34:06.753 --> 34:09.715
- ♪ I'M THE QUEEN
OF THE DARK SIDE ♪

34:09.715 --> 34:13.010
♪ HE'S THE KING OF THE FOOLS ♪

34:13.010 --> 34:15.637
♪ TICK TICK ♪

34:15.637 --> 34:18.557
♪ BOOM BOOM BOOM ♪

34:18.557 --> 34:20.642
♪ SEDUCTION SIRENS ♪

34:20.642 --> 34:24.771
♪ GET THE MONEY AND RUN ♪

34:24.771 --> 34:27.191
♪ LISTEN FOR THE SOUND ♪

34:27.191 --> 34:35.657
♪ ♪

34:35.657 --> 34:38.243
♪ WE WANT THE SIGHTS ♪

34:38.243 --> 34:42.080
♪ ♪

34:42.080 --> 34:43.665
- YOU NEED SOMETHING?

34:43.665 --> 34:46.418
- HMM?

34:46.418 --> 34:48.629
- WAITING CAN BE VERY STRESSFUL.

34:48.629 --> 34:52.216
- OH, YEAH.
[chuckles]

34:52.216 --> 34:54.801
- ♪ OW ♪

34:54.801 --> 34:56.053
♪ HITCH A RIDE TO ARIZONA ♪

34:56.053 --> 34:58.222
- MMM.

34:58.222 --> 35:00.182
100 FOR THE MOUTH,

35:00.182 --> 35:03.936
200 FOR THE--
[clicks tongue]

35:03.936 --> 35:06.813
[chuckles]

35:06.813 --> 35:08.232
- YOU THINK WE HAVE ENOUGH TIME?

35:08.232 --> 35:10.067
I MEAN, I DON'T WANT
TO MISS THE BIRTH OF...

35:10.067 --> 35:11.360
- OH, YEAH.

35:11.360 --> 35:15.281
BABY TAKES HOURS TO COME.

35:15.281 --> 35:17.157
- ♪ THIS IS THE SOUND ♪

35:17.157 --> 35:20.160
[rock music]

35:20.160 --> 35:28.168
♪ ♪

35:33.465 --> 35:36.009
- BABY NEEDS A NEW PAIR
OF SHOES, RIGHT?

35:39.221 --> 35:41.974
BACK IN A FLASH WITH THE CASH.

35:47.145 --> 35:49.982
[shushing]

35:56.364 --> 35:59.157
HOW'S IT GOING, GUYS?
CAN I GET A SMOKE?

35:59.157 --> 36:02.286
LET'S TAKE A WALK?

36:02.286 --> 36:05.122
♪ ♪

36:05.122 --> 36:09.293
- [crying]

36:09.293 --> 36:16.842
♪ ♪

36:16.842 --> 36:19.428
- HI, IT'S OKAY.

36:19.428 --> 36:24.308
- [groaning]

36:24.308 --> 36:26.351
[weakly]
HELP. HELP.

36:29.313 --> 36:30.355
ANYBODY.

36:30.355 --> 36:32.316
- WE NEED TO FIND
SOMETHING FILTHY

36:32.316 --> 36:34.443
AND RIPPED TO PUT ON LIAM.

36:34.443 --> 36:37.195
THE FOOD BANK AT THE METHODISTS
ALWAYS GIVE US EXTRA STUFF

36:37.195 --> 36:38.780
IF THEY THINK WE'RE HOMELESS.
- HELP ME.

36:38.780 --> 36:40.365
HELP ME.
I CAN'T GET UP.

36:40.365 --> 36:42.743
HELP.
I NEED HELP!

36:42.743 --> 36:44.287
- YOU BEEN TAKING YOUR MEDS?

36:44.287 --> 36:45.912
- HAVE YOU BEEN
GIVING THEM TO ME?

36:45.912 --> 36:48.332
- NOT MY JOB.
YOUR JOB.

36:48.332 --> 36:50.584
YOU DON'T CARE FOR YOUR FAMILY--
CAN'T EVEN MAKE SURE

36:50.584 --> 36:53.003
CHUCKIE AND ME HAVE
A ROOF OVER OUR HEADS,

36:53.003 --> 36:55.047
BUT WE'RE SUPPOSED
TO TAKE CARE OF YOU?

36:55.047 --> 36:56.382
OKAY, HANDS UP.

36:56.382 --> 36:57.507
SKIN TURN YELLOW?

36:57.507 --> 36:58.967
- A BIT, YEAH.

36:58.967 --> 37:01.303
- PROBABLY REJECTING YOUR LIVER.
- [groans]

37:01.303 --> 37:04.348
- OKAY, CHUCKIE, YOU FINISH
GETTING DRESSED, OKAY?

37:04.348 --> 37:05.891
NOTHING NICE.

37:05.891 --> 37:09.312
OOH, MAYBE THAT SHIRT
WITH THE BLOODSTAINS ON IT

37:09.312 --> 37:12.105
FROM WHEN
YOU TRIED SKATEBOARDING?

37:12.105 --> 37:14.524
- CHUCK-O, HELP YOUR OLD PAP,
WILL YOU?

37:14.524 --> 37:16.109
HUH?
HELP ME.

37:16.109 --> 37:18.111
- AND DON'T HELP
YOUR GRANDFATHER, CHUCKIE.

37:18.111 --> 37:19.696
HE DOESN'T CARE ABOUT US.

37:19.696 --> 37:21.114
- CHUCK.

37:22.741 --> 37:26.370
LIAM, GET ME THE PHONE,
HUH, BUDDY?

37:26.370 --> 37:28.288
FRUIT OF MY LOIN,

37:28.288 --> 37:29.831
APPLE OF YOUR PAPPY'S EYE?

37:29.831 --> 37:32.418
- YOU TOO, LIAM.
DON'T HELP HIM!

37:32.418 --> 37:36.422
- LIAM, HELP--
[grunts]

37:36.422 --> 37:38.507
JESUS.

37:38.507 --> 37:41.510
[grunting]

37:44.971 --> 37:47.641
LITTLE COCOA INGRATE.

37:47.641 --> 37:50.977
[groaning]

37:50.977 --> 37:52.396
FUCK.

37:52.396 --> 37:55.399
[grunting]

38:06.535 --> 38:07.828
[shouts]

38:07.828 --> 38:09.121
[groaning]

38:09.121 --> 38:13.500
[dial tone]

38:13.500 --> 38:15.127
[line beeping]

38:15.127 --> 38:18.130
- [crying]

38:22.343 --> 38:23.969
[tires screeching]

38:23.969 --> 38:25.429
- THAT'S HIM.
- HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:25.429 --> 38:26.972
- THIS YOUR CAR, SIR?
- OH.

38:26.972 --> 38:28.306
- SIR, YOU CAN'T LEAVE
A BABY ALONE

38:28.306 --> 38:30.016
IN A LOCKED CAR ON A HOT DAY.

38:30.016 --> 38:32.060
- I SAW HIM GET INTO A CAR
WITH A MAN AND JUST DRIVE OFF.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.353
- YOU'RE SCARING THE SHIT
OUT OF HIM.

38:33.353 --> 38:35.105
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:35.105 --> 38:37.566
- SIR, WE WERE CONCERNED
FOR THE SAFETY OF THE CHILD.

38:37.566 --> 38:38.859
- YOU CALLED THE COPS?

38:38.859 --> 38:40.819
I GET INTO A CAR FOR ONE SECOND,

38:40.819 --> 38:42.237
AND YOU CALL THE COPS?

38:42.237 --> 38:43.405
ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING ME,
LADY?

38:43.405 --> 38:44.781
- HEY, SHE DID THE RIGHT THING.

38:44.781 --> 38:46.825
SIR, NOW,
WHY DON'T YOU CALM DOWN?

38:46.825 --> 38:48.452
- CALM DOWN?
YOU'RE TELLING ME TO CALM DOWN?

38:48.452 --> 38:51.413
TRYING TO STEAL MY BABY,
TELLING ME TO CALM DOWN?

38:51.413 --> 38:53.206
- ARE YOU ON SOMETHING, SIR?
DRUGS?

38:53.206 --> 38:55.792
- DRUGS? DRUGS?
AM I ON FUCKING DRUGS?

38:55.792 --> 38:57.836
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S TRYING TO STEAL MY BABY!

38:57.836 --> 38:59.504
YOU'RE THE BABY THIEVES.

38:59.504 --> 39:01.465
YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT'S TRYING TO TAKE MY BABY.

39:01.465 --> 39:02.549
WHAT THE FUCK IS WRONG WITH YOU?

39:02.549 --> 39:03.800
WHO SENT YOU?

39:03.800 --> 39:05.302
JESUS SEND YOU?

39:05.302 --> 39:06.470
DID JESUS SEND YOU
TO TAKE MY BABY?

39:06.470 --> 39:08.013
- NOBODY SENT US.

39:08.013 --> 39:09.556
SIR, WE'RE JUST HERE TO HELP,
OKAY?

39:09.556 --> 39:11.683
- DON'T FUCKING LIE TO ME!
WHY DID HE SEND YOU?

39:11.683 --> 39:13.185
- WHY DON'T WE HAVE A SEAT
AND TALK?

39:13.185 --> 39:15.479
- GET THE FUCK AWAY FROM ME.
STAY AWAY!

39:15.479 --> 39:18.190
- [groans]
- SIR, STOP!

39:18.190 --> 39:19.400
STOP!

39:19.400 --> 39:22.403
[rock music]

39:22.403 --> 39:26.615
♪ ♪

39:26.615 --> 39:28.241
- TAKE THE FRONT!

39:28.241 --> 39:31.537
♪ ♪

39:31.537 --> 39:32.538
- HELP ME!

39:32.538 --> 39:33.663
THEY WANT TO STEAL MY BABY!

39:33.663 --> 39:34.956
THEY'RE TRYING TO STEAL HIM!

39:34.956 --> 39:36.708
THEY'RE GABRIEL'S DEMONS.

39:36.708 --> 39:39.669
THEY'RE TRYING TO TAKE HIM!
PLEASE!

39:39.669 --> 39:41.547
HELP ME!
PLEASE, PLEASE HELP ME!

39:41.547 --> 39:44.508
HELP ME, HELP ME,
HELP ME, HELP ME!

39:44.508 --> 39:48.345
NO TESTS! NO TESTS!
NO, NO, NO, NO!

39:48.345 --> 39:49.930
NO TESTS, DON'T TEST ME!
- [crying]

39:49.930 --> 39:51.890
- STAY AWAY!
STAY AWAY!

39:51.890 --> 39:55.143
NOT FAIR!
PLEASE, PLEASE.

39:55.143 --> 39:57.896
I'M SO SORRY.
I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.

39:57.896 --> 40:00.565
PLEASE.
I'M SO SORRY.

40:02.067 --> 40:03.652
[knock at door]

40:08.198 --> 40:09.950
[knock at door]

40:20.752 --> 40:22.463
- WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:22.463 --> 40:24.465
- I WAS RUNNING AN ERRAND
DOWN THE BLOCK FOR WORK.

40:24.465 --> 40:26.467
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT HAVE
HEARD SOMETHING FROM IAN.

40:26.467 --> 40:29.135
- NO.
- OH, A BERETTA PX4 STORM.

40:29.135 --> 40:30.637
- DON'T TOUCH IT.

40:30.637 --> 40:32.973
- SO NOTHING FROM IAN?

40:32.973 --> 40:34.641
- WHAT THE FUCK DO YOU THINK?

40:34.641 --> 40:36.726
- SAW IT A COUPLE TIMES
WITH MY MOM, MONICA.

40:36.726 --> 40:38.687
KIND OF SCARY,
WEIRD STUFF.

40:38.687 --> 40:40.230
SHE CLIMBED TO THE TOP
OF OUR ROOF

40:40.230 --> 40:42.190
AND THOUGHT SHE WAS A BIRD.

40:42.190 --> 40:43.483
- SHE JUMP?
- NO.

40:43.483 --> 40:46.194
THE FIREMEN CAME
AND GOT HER DOWN.

40:55.996 --> 40:58.123
- YOU WANT A BEER?
- SURE.

41:00.834 --> 41:02.878
- YOU GOT ANY WEED?
HEARD YOU'RE WORKING A CORNER.

41:02.878 --> 41:05.964
- SMOKING THE PRODUCT IS
BAD BUSINESS, EATS INTO PROFITS.

41:05.964 --> 41:07.550
- GOOD THINKING, KID.

41:07.550 --> 41:09.426
YOU MIGHT JUST MAKE IT
OUT THERE.

41:09.426 --> 41:12.637
NOT A WHITE MAN'S GAME ANYMORE,
THOUGH.

41:17.309 --> 41:18.560
[burps]

41:18.560 --> 41:20.103
[clattering]

41:20.103 --> 41:21.771
TWO POINTS.
[phone ringing]

41:25.191 --> 41:27.653
YEAH.

41:27.653 --> 41:29.696
YEAH.

41:29.696 --> 41:31.031
OKAY.

41:31.031 --> 41:33.033
COPS GOT IAN AND THE BABY.

41:34.492 --> 41:35.911
WHERE THE FUCK'S TERRE HAUTE?

41:39.497 --> 41:42.250
- SO HOW LONG ARE WE GONNA WAIT?
- A LITTLE BIT LONGER.

41:42.250 --> 41:45.503
- ARE YOU SURE
SHE STILL CARES ABOUT YOU?

41:45.503 --> 41:47.047
- YES.

41:47.047 --> 41:48.716
- WE GOT TO LEAVE
FOR DUBAI SOON.

41:48.716 --> 41:49.925
- I KNOW.
- VERY SOON.

41:49.925 --> 41:51.259
- I KNOW.

41:51.259 --> 41:52.595
HERE SHE IS.

41:54.554 --> 41:56.682
BEEN CALLING YOU FOR HOURS.

41:56.682 --> 41:58.516
- I HAD A TOUGH DAY.

41:58.516 --> 42:00.143
- IAN?

42:03.438 --> 42:04.814
LOOK, WE GOT TO TALK.

42:04.814 --> 42:07.025
- I'M NOT SURE
I'M UP FOR IT TONIGHT.

42:16.326 --> 42:18.328
FUCK, MY PHONE'S DEAD.

42:21.707 --> 42:25.043
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

42:25.043 --> 42:27.337
- THEN DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

42:30.173 --> 42:32.467
- WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

42:32.467 --> 42:33.551
- MY PHONE CHARGER.

42:33.551 --> 42:35.053
SOMEBODY'S ALWAYS TAKING IT.

42:35.053 --> 42:37.347
FUCK.

42:37.347 --> 42:38.766
- I'M SORRY.

42:38.766 --> 42:41.351
- FUCKING SAMMI, PROBABLY.
SHIT.

42:41.351 --> 42:43.770
- NO, I'M SORRY FOR EVERYTHING
THAT'S HAPPENED.

42:45.271 --> 42:46.690
- [chuckles]

42:48.858 --> 42:50.860
[bottle cap clattering]

42:50.860 --> 42:53.780
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO BE ENOUGH?

42:53.780 --> 42:56.116
- I SHOULD HAVE BEEN HERE.
- YEAH.

42:56.116 --> 42:58.744
YEAH, YOU SHOULD HAVE.

42:58.744 --> 43:00.161
- I THOUGHT ABOUT YOU
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

43:00.161 --> 43:01.622
- DON'T.

43:01.622 --> 43:03.373
YOU LEFT.
YOU DIDN'T COME BACK.

43:03.373 --> 43:06.543
- HEY, I LOVE YOU.

43:06.543 --> 43:08.754
- DON'T DO THAT AGAIN.

43:08.754 --> 43:09.963
- I LOVE YOU.

43:09.963 --> 43:13.717
I LOVE EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU.
- PLEASE.

43:13.717 --> 43:15.510
- I AM SO...
- WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME?

43:15.510 --> 43:16.886
- SO SORRY.

43:23.309 --> 43:25.311
I LOVE YOU.

43:27.313 --> 43:28.606
[whispers]
I LOVE YOU.

43:30.817 --> 43:33.820
[rock music]

43:33.820 --> 43:41.828
♪ ♪

43:43.747 --> 43:44.998
- ♪ TAKE ME AROUND ♪

43:44.998 --> 43:46.958
♪ AROUND YOUR END OF TOWN ♪

43:46.958 --> 43:49.961
♪ 'CAUSE I'M STRUGGLING TO KEEP
MY FEET ON THE GROUND ♪

43:49.961 --> 43:51.755
- [grunting]

43:51.755 --> 43:53.214
- ♪ WHEN YOU WERE NAKED
AND DEFLATED ♪

43:53.214 --> 43:55.633
♪ I THOUGHT THAT WE WERE
THE GREATEST ♪

43:55.633 --> 43:57.260
♪ I WONDER WHY I LEFT YOU ♪

43:57.260 --> 43:59.262
♪ WHY I LET YOU DOWN ♪

43:59.262 --> 44:01.765
♪ YOU'VE GOTTA CRUSH ME BABE ♪

44:01.765 --> 44:03.600
♪ GRIND ME DOWN ♪

44:03.600 --> 44:07.687
♪ TREAT ME LIKE I DON'T
PLAY AROUND ♪

44:07.687 --> 44:10.816
- [sobbing]

44:10.816 --> 44:14.027
- ♪ TREAT ME LIKE
I DON'T GO OFF ♪

44:14.027 --> 44:16.696
♪ YOU'VE GOTTA CRUSH ME BABY ♪

44:16.696 --> 44:19.699
♪ GRIND ME DOWN ♪

44:19.699 --> 44:21.827
- STOP.

44:21.827 --> 44:23.328
PLEASE, JIMMY, STOP.

44:23.328 --> 44:24.621
STOP.

44:24.621 --> 44:26.164
JIMMY, STOP!

44:28.041 --> 44:31.044
[crying]

44:44.307 --> 44:46.893
JUST PLEASE...GO HOME.

44:50.814 --> 44:53.399
GO HOME.

44:53.399 --> 44:54.776
- [exhales deeply]

45:12.836 --> 45:14.671
[line ringing]

45:14.671 --> 45:15.755
- FUCK.

45:15.755 --> 45:17.173
- FIONA?

45:17.173 --> 45:18.884
- I'M JUST
GETTING HER VOICE MAIL.

45:18.884 --> 45:20.593
- YOU WANT ME TO TRY
TEXTING HER AGAIN?

45:20.593 --> 45:22.095
- CAN'T HURT.

45:24.890 --> 45:26.766
- I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD HAVE LISTENED TO YOU.

45:26.766 --> 45:29.227
- YEAH, YOU SHOULD HAVE.

45:29.227 --> 45:31.229
- I DIDN'T KNOW
THINGS COULD GET THIS BAD.

45:31.229 --> 45:32.856
- CAN GET WORSE.

45:34.607 --> 45:35.901
GET MUCH WORSE.

45:42.282 --> 45:45.660
[heart monitor beeping]

45:45.660 --> 45:46.953
- MR. GALLAGHER?

45:48.746 --> 45:50.081
HOW YOU FEELING, FRANK?

45:50.081 --> 45:51.583
- I'VE FELT BETTER.

45:51.583 --> 45:53.126
- I WOULD HOPE SO.

45:53.126 --> 45:54.795
WE'VE STARTED YOU ON PREDNISONE

45:54.795 --> 45:56.754
TO DECREASE THE INFLAMMATION
IN YOUR LIVER,

45:56.754 --> 45:58.840
ALSO LASIX TO BRING DOWN
YOUR FLUID LEVELS.

45:58.840 --> 46:00.758
YOU WERE QUITE JAUNDICED
WHEN YOU ARRIVED.

46:00.758 --> 46:02.552
HAVE YOU BEEN TAKING
YOUR ANTIREJECTION MEDS

46:02.552 --> 46:03.846
AS PRESCRIBED?

46:03.846 --> 46:05.722
- MY BITCH
OF A NEWFOUND DAUGHTER

46:05.722 --> 46:07.432
HASN'T BEEN GIVING THEM TO ME.

46:07.432 --> 46:10.226
- YOUR DAUGHTER HAS BEEN KEEPING
YOUR MEDICATIONS AWAY FROM YOU?

46:10.226 --> 46:13.354
- NO, BUT SHE WAS SUPPOSED
TO MAKE SURE I TAKE THEM.

46:13.354 --> 46:15.983
- MR. GALLAGHER,
YOU ARE A 51-YEAR-OLD MAN

46:15.983 --> 46:17.358
WITH A NEW LIVER TRANSPLANT.

46:17.358 --> 46:19.110
YOU SHOULD BE ABLE
TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY

46:19.110 --> 46:20.570
FOR YOUR OWN MEDICATIONS,

46:20.570 --> 46:23.907
UNLESS YOU'RE
MENTALLY INCAPACITATED.

46:23.907 --> 46:26.869
ARE YOU MENTALLY INCAPACITATED?

46:26.869 --> 46:28.453
- MENTALLY INCAPACITATED?

46:28.453 --> 46:30.580
- RETARDED.
ARE YOU RETARDED, FRANK?

46:30.580 --> 46:31.915
- NO.

46:31.915 --> 46:34.125
- THEN GET YOUR SHIT TOGETHER.

46:38.964 --> 46:40.506
- AM I GONNA LOSE THE LIVER?

46:40.506 --> 46:44.302
- NO, BUT WE RAN A TOX SCREEN
AND BLOOD ALCOHOL LEVEL

46:44.302 --> 46:46.012
AS PART OF YOUR WORKUP
ON ADMITTANCE.

46:46.012 --> 46:47.805
I WAS HAPPILY SURPRISED
TO FIND THERE WAS

46:47.805 --> 46:48.890
NO ALCOHOL IN YOUR SYSTEM.

46:48.890 --> 46:50.391
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

46:50.391 --> 46:51.893
- HOWEVER, WE DID FIND
TRACES OF COCAINE,

46:51.893 --> 46:53.811
MARIJUANA, AND OPIATES.

46:53.811 --> 46:56.773
IF I WERE TO HAZARD A GUESS,
MY MONEY WOULD BE ON OXYCONTIN.

46:56.773 --> 46:59.150
- GREAT...STUFF.

46:59.150 --> 47:01.569
THE GUY WHO INVENTED IT SHOULD
BE ON THE NOBEL SHORT LIST.

47:01.569 --> 47:02.946
- THIS IS NO JOKE, FRANK.

47:02.946 --> 47:04.865
SOMEBODY GAVE THEIR LIFE,
SO YOU COULD LIVE.

47:04.865 --> 47:08.952
- WELL, TECHNICALLY,
I THINK HE WAS PRETTY MUCH DEAD

47:08.952 --> 47:12.956
BEFORE THEY STARTED
DIVVYING UP THE BODY PARTS.

47:12.956 --> 47:15.083
- I'M LOADING YOU UP
ON ANTIBIOTICS

47:15.083 --> 47:17.543
AND A NEW ROUND
OF ANTIREJECTION MEDS,

47:17.543 --> 47:20.129
AND I'LL BE SENDING YOU HOME
IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.

47:20.129 --> 47:22.131
BUT IF YOU DON'T TAKE CARE
OF THIS LIVER,

47:22.131 --> 47:23.633
YOU'RE SHIT OUT OF LUCK.

47:23.633 --> 47:24.884
NOBODY'S GIVING YOU
ANOTHER ONE.

47:24.884 --> 47:27.887
[rock music]

47:27.887 --> 47:35.895
♪ ♪

47:36.938 --> 47:39.107
[dog barking]

47:42.235 --> 47:43.569
- ARE YOU COMING?

47:43.569 --> 47:45.154
- I SHOULD PROBABLY STAY
IN THE CAR.

47:45.154 --> 47:46.572
- WHY?

47:46.572 --> 47:49.784
- I MIGHT HAVE
A POUND OF WEED ON ME.

47:49.784 --> 47:52.996
- JESUS CHRIST, THAT'S A POUND?
- GIVE OR TAKE.

47:52.996 --> 47:54.664
- ALL RIGHT,
THEN YOU CAN STAY IN THE CAR,

47:54.664 --> 47:56.874
BUT WE'RE GONNA TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER, ALL RIGHT?

48:03.798 --> 48:05.591
HEY, EXCUSE ME?

48:05.591 --> 48:08.177
I-I GOT A CALL ABOUT MY BROTHER
BEING IN HERE, IAN GALLAGHER?

48:08.177 --> 48:10.596
- YEAH, THAT'S ME.
I WAS THE ARRESTING OFFICER.

48:10.596 --> 48:12.932
DOES YOUR BROTHER HAVE
A HISTORY OF MENTAL ILLNESS?

48:12.932 --> 48:14.434
- YES.

48:14.434 --> 48:15.935
- HE WAS ACTING IRRATIONALLY,

48:15.935 --> 48:18.146
LEFT A BABY LOCKED
INSIDE OF A HOT CAR,

48:18.146 --> 48:20.106
AND THEN HE RAN AWAY
WHEN WE TRIED TO QUESTION HIM.

48:20.106 --> 48:21.399
- IS THE BABY OKAY?

48:21.399 --> 48:23.192
- YEAH, HE'S SLEEPING IN BACK.

48:23.192 --> 48:25.028
IS THE BABY YOUR BROTHER'S BABY?

48:25.028 --> 48:26.404
- NO, HE'S MINE.

48:26.404 --> 48:28.072
- YOU'RE THE FATHER?

48:28.072 --> 48:30.366
WHO ARE YOU IN RELATIONSHIP
TO MR. GALLAGHER?

48:30.366 --> 48:32.660
- HIS PARTNER.

48:32.660 --> 48:35.038
LOVER? FAMILY?
YOU KNOW?

48:36.664 --> 48:38.082
- WHEN WE TOOK MR. GALLAGHER
TO THE E.R.,

48:38.082 --> 48:40.084
THEY GAVE HIM A SEDATIVE,
SEEMED TO CALM HIM DOWN,

48:40.084 --> 48:42.045
BUT HE'S CLEARLY A TROUBLED KID.

48:42.045 --> 48:43.379
- IS HE UNDER ARREST?

48:43.379 --> 48:45.214
- HE'LL HAVE
TO FACE SOME CHARGES,

48:45.214 --> 48:47.592
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA HOLD HIM,
BUT HIS CAR WENT TO IMPOUND.

48:47.592 --> 48:49.844
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO GET THAT
PROCESSED FOR A COUPLE DAYS,

48:49.844 --> 48:52.097
AND YOU'LL HAVE
TO PAY THE TOW CHARGES.

48:52.097 --> 48:54.307
YOU NEED TO GET HIM SOME HELP.

48:54.307 --> 48:57.019
- YES, SIR, WE, UH--
WE KNOW.

49:07.362 --> 49:10.239
HEY. HEY. HEY.

49:11.449 --> 49:12.784
ALL RIGHT?

49:34.222 --> 49:35.723
- YOURS?

49:37.016 --> 49:39.186
HE'S A CUTE KID.
GOOD SLEEPER TOO.

49:39.186 --> 49:41.896
GOT ONE ABOUT HIS AGE AT HOME.

49:41.896 --> 49:44.357
YOU'RE A LUCKY MAN.

49:44.357 --> 49:46.943
- HEY.

49:46.943 --> 49:49.153
YES, SIR.
THANK YOU.

49:49.153 --> 49:51.781
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

49:51.781 --> 49:54.784
[somber music]

49:54.784 --> 50:02.792
♪ ♪

50:04.544 --> 50:06.087
- [sighs]

50:19.142 --> 50:22.770
- ♪ YOU TOOK MY HAND AND BROUGHT
ME DOWN IN THE MORNING ♪

50:22.770 --> 50:26.607
♪ AND I WAS SITTING
WAITING FOR THE TELEPHONE ♪

50:26.607 --> 50:31.112
♪ TO SWALLOW ME WHOLE ♪

50:31.112 --> 50:37.660
♪ ♪

50:37.660 --> 50:39.745
♪ I SAW YOUR FACE REFLECTED ♪

50:39.745 --> 50:41.914
♪ ON THE RESONANT SCREEN ♪

50:41.914 --> 50:46.502
♪ AND I WATCHED YOUR MOUTH
MOVING LIKE A TIRED MACHINE ♪

50:46.502 --> 50:50.423
♪ TRYING TO PLEAD WITH ME ♪

50:50.423 --> 50:56.804
♪ TRYING TO SWALLOW ME WHOLE ♪

50:56.804 --> 51:04.729
♪ ♪

51:21.496 --> 51:25.292
♪ IT'S BEEN A WHILE SINCE
I'VE BEEN GONE AND AWAY ♪

51:25.292 --> 51:29.712
♪ AND I WATCHED YOUR EYES
REFLECT ME IN A TERRIBLE WAY ♪

51:29.712 --> 51:34.008
♪ AS YOU CAST YOUR GAZE ♪

51:34.008 --> 51:37.512
♪ TO THE FLICKERING HALL ♪

51:37.512 --> 51:40.515
[both breathing heavily]

51:40.515 --> 51:44.101
♪ AND YOU KNELT BESIDE ME
AND YOU STARTED TO PRAY ♪

51:44.101 --> 51:47.021
♪ AND THE WHITES
OF YOUR EYES BLACKENED ♪

51:47.021 --> 51:49.106
♪ WITH A HARDENED DECAY ♪

51:49.106 --> 51:53.195
♪ AND YOU TALKED TO ME ♪

51:53.195 --> 51:57.240
♪ IN A BROKEN VOICE ♪

51:57.240 --> 52:02.287
♪ IN YOUR OPEN MOUTH
SILENCE ME IN THE COURSING ♪

52:02.287 --> 52:04.080
♪ BLOOD IN MY EYES ♪

52:04.080 --> 52:06.291
♪ DRESS ME IN YOUR CLOTHES ♪

52:06.291 --> 52:10.212
♪ AND SWALLOW ME WHOLE ♪

52:10.212 --> 52:16.343
♪ SWALLOW ME WHOLE ♪

52:16.343 --> 52:24.141
♪ ♪

52:24.141 --> 52:28.646
[baby cooing]

52:28.646 --> 52:32.233
- WE NEED TO GET HIM COMMITTED
EVEN IF HE DOESN'T WANT TO GO.

52:32.233 --> 52:36.362
WE CAN JUST...TELL THEM THAT
HE KIDNAPPED THE KID, RIGHT?

52:36.362 --> 52:38.155
THEY HAVE TO TAKE HIM.

52:38.155 --> 52:41.158
THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOME KIND OF, LIKE,

52:41.158 --> 52:43.160
"DANGER TO OTHERS" LAW, RIGHT?

52:43.160 --> 52:44.912
- NO.
IT COULD BE COMPLICATED.

52:44.912 --> 52:46.455
- WELL, IF HE WON'T GO,
I'M JUST GONNA CALL

52:46.455 --> 52:47.748
THE FUCKING COPS ON HIM,

52:47.748 --> 52:49.333
TELL THEM
THAT HE STOLE THE BABY.

52:49.333 --> 52:51.211
THEY'LL--

52:51.211 --> 52:53.213
THEY'LL PUT HIM AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

